start application:

Research analytics only:
- public-data anomaly monitoring and explanation
- no trading, execution, wallet, or account actions
- outputs are suspicious-activity research signals, not legal determinations

Terminal	Command
cd server && python -m uvicorn main:app --reload

# start event cache (refreshes current active events used by --all-events)
python -m model.event_cache 

# monitor specific events (defaults: min_abs=0.03, min_rel=0.08)
python -m model.insider_detection 2890 3100 --interval 5

# monitor ALL active events from the database cache
# defaults become stricter with --all-events: min_abs=0.05, min_rel=0.10
python -m model.insider_detection --all-events --max-events 500 (--all-events calls database/events.py with get_all_event_ids())

# keep the news dataset fresh every 5 minutes
python -m news_scraper.main --loop --interval-seconds 300

# validate or replay frozen trigger payloads from a JSONL export
python -m model.replay_evaluation --input path/to/triggers.jsonl

python3 -m model.cross_asset_predictions --min-score 70 --limit 500

source .venv/bin/activate
streamlit run gui/app.py # set OLLAMA_API_KEY / OLLAMA_MODEL in the shell if using the explanation layer